<br>
Mills on the Rathe (Bmills post Zeb split) was charging res when he was one of the first high level cleric.  He gave resses for free to friends though (I was not one of them) but the 30pp at the time was well worth paying out to save lost time from death.<br>
<br>
Things seems much inflated nowadays that plats don't mean so much until you pool all the cost a cleric accumulates.  How many clerics carry 200 peridots at any given time?  Not many I woud think.<br>
<br>
IMO:<br>
- ressing a corpse infront of me when I have a res stick should not warrant a charge.<br>
- ressing a corpse dragged infront of me when I have a res stick should not warrant a charge.  but if I have to wait there x minutes for my time when I have other things to do... perhaps some coins is fair. but for me, i won't.<br>
- ressing some player(s) who died in a nearby zone/port zone, and offered me x thousand pp and can afford it, well i'm not that &quot;honorable and stoopid&quot; to refuse their generousity when I can down that same plat straight to a backpack full of peridots.<br>
<br>
- I would refure plats from others, but I won't refuse peridots.  Is that like finding a usable stamp and keep it, but finding money may bring some form of 'guilt' ? <br>
<br>
(bored at work)<br>
